        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 3 at 5:27PM PDT until June 3 at 7:30PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM PDT, Rainfall totals of up to one inch were recorded near
Grapevine Springs and near Corn Creek. Flash Flooding remains
possible.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Las Vegas, Rainbow Canyon, Mt. Charleston, Spring Mountains,
Hilltop Campground, Mahogany Grove Campground, Kyle Canyon
Campground, Fletcher View Campground, Dolomite Campground and
Mcwilliams Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
